reviews.text: The salad bar was dirty and out of salad mix, ranch, and several other items. The floors were really sticky and everybody who walked across them made those gross sounds of shoes sticking. Their ice cream would not work and they had several items out that they didn't refill the entire time we were there. It's over priced for the food you receive. Overall not a good visit.

This is where my son wanted to go for his 12th birthday and we loved it. Friendly staff and food was always kept up hot fresh and filled and busier kept tables cleaned. Very impressed with services and will be back. We were a family of 8 with 6 of them being kids ages 9 to 15 !

We arrived at 10:06 AM, just a few minutes after they opened at 10:00. When we got there, they told us they were still working on the pizzas and that they would be ready ‚Äúsoon.‚Äù We waited patiently, then asked if we could get some fried chicken ‚Äî only to be told we would have to wait again for it to be cooked. Later, we asked about dessert, and they said it would be ready soon as well. After waiting for almost an hour, we were told they had forgotten to even put the dessert in the oven.
To make things worse, the lady at the register told us they weren‚Äôt cooking much because there were only a few customers ‚Äî but if that‚Äôs the case, why charge us full price?
Overall, a very disappointing and frustrating experience.
First time going. The general manager Max definitely helped me out and even made me my own pizza. I guess is available to everybody and anyone. That‚Äôs fire. He also recommended it. Fire üî•

Tara!!! Was amazing lover her a lot and this place PIZZA RANCH! Its like a mini Thanksgiving buffet daily, I love being able to order special pizza and getting first dibs having it brought to my table with cozy jamsss!!

detailedReviews.text: Trash! This place is so overly hyped it's repulsive...So many people raved about that place that I took my family of six there for dinner today and to all of our surprise this place is a knockoff pizza street. There was literally only about six pizzas to choose from and an odd selection of a poor excuse for Sunday dinner including fried chicken, mash potatoes with gravy, stuffing and green beans...the chicken was surprisingly good but everything else was extremely bland and what I imagine dinner would taste at non -melanated people's house. The pizza that we hoped was as delicious as everyone raved about probably was good at some point YEARS ago but now it is such a sorry excuse for a pizza joint even the kids rated it a solid 2/10. Would NEVER return

detailedReviews.author: Chase Poore
detailedReviews.text:
I'll start this off simple,  There's a reason this chain is dying. Parking is the best part.  Easy enough to find a spot, but good lord 20$ a person for pizza street quality pizza is wild.  I'm glad I didn't bring my wife and kid. For nostalgia reasons I decided to stay and satisfy my hunger. But I'll admit it was hard not to leave when I saw the absolute disarray that surrounded me while I ate my overcooked and obviously aged pizza. As of now I sit in what appears to be the only somewhat wiped down table in this nearly empty restaurant. Almost tempted to time how long it will take then to clean numerous cups and crumbs of the surrounding areas. Food and various garbage litters the floor,  but at least the sweet sound of George Micheal lingers over my head from the speaker. (20 minutes since my arrival on the cups by the way.) It has been almost ten years since I was last in a Pizza Ranch. I think I'll try again in another decade to see if it improves. If they survive that long of course.

In summation:
‚Ä¢Pizza is better elsewhere and cheaper.

‚Ä¢Atmosphere is dead and gives depression.

‚Ä¢Cleanliness is borderline concerning.

‚Ä¢Staff was living but not lively, but that's not really thier fault. I take it as a symptom of working here.

detailedReviews.author: Karen Howard
detailedReviews.text:
This was the first time we stopped in for the Thursday Wing Night.
We got their before the rush, and the cashier, mentioned it had been slow all day.
I went to the table my husband picked, I look down at see trash on the floor in two sections of the Dining Area where customers sit, had  food & cup lid on the floor & other trash.
‚ñ™Ô∏éSo I think to myself, if they were so Slow why is the Dining Floor so Dirty.
‚ñ™Ô∏é I got some of the Different Wings: they were all cold. (not a one was "Hot" in Temperature.
‚ñ™Ô∏é I am sorry this location dropped the ball Big Time.
‚ñ™Ô∏éThen I also got 2 chicken legs, they were hot "Temperature", I bite into them, and both of them: not cooked right, they were "Both Raw" in the middle, so of course (I spit back into a napkin). My husband got lucky and his Chicken Breast was hot & cooked correctly. No potato wedges or waffle fries. The stuffing & gravy were good also.
‚ñ™Ô∏éWhen we got there the Pizza buffet area was "Already Empty", they didn't have desert pizza or chocolate chip cookie either.
The Salad Bar (was Out of lettuce- iceberg kind, and bearly had any of the other kind). Grated cheese & mushrooms were both almost out. No boiled Eggs (Use to have them).
‚ñ™Ô∏éThey now had spot that had Coleslaw & Macaroni salad. (I tried the Macaroni salad it was good).
I got the French dressing, it was like Watered Down (So sad)........
‚ñ™Ô∏éThey didn't even have "Lids" that Fit the containers where the coleslaw & macaroni on the salad bar.
‚ñ™Ô∏éNo apples or oranges on the salad bar either.
They never kept the desert Bar filled the entire time we were there..
‚ñ™Ô∏éIt was sad, folks pay good money to eat out,  and provide a Meal for their families, and Get this Kind Bad of Service.
‚ñ™Ô∏éThe Best Thing they had was a "Rootbeer Float" that I made up myself. Thank goodness there Soft Serve Ice Cream machine was working ‚òÜ‚òÜ‚òÜ.
‚ñ™Ô∏éI don't know if this location is under new management or they have No staff, This Location Needs some Major Help, So Beware.‚ñ™Ô∏é‚ñ™Ô∏é‚ñ™Ô∏é‚ñ™Ô∏é‚ñ™Ô∏é
‚ñ™Ô∏éHope management looks at their reviews.
